Requirements:
1. Node.js
2. npm (node package manager)

---------------------------------

Install Node.js
    Windows: https://nodejs.org/en/download/
    Linux: https://nodejs.org/en/download/package-manager/

---------------------------------

Guide for Windows:
1. Run cmd
2. Go to your project from command line (Example: 'cd D:\Projects\scrappy-demo') and press enter
3. From project directory type 'node scrappy.js http://somesite.com' in command line
    (Example: 'node scrappy.js https://www.youmagine.com/designs/lampe')
4. And see result in https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1s0dl-7vjKGrYjwaMBlD88uEJaAeVk0l2ttyszUKjTOU/edit#gid=0

Guide for Linux:
1. Run cmd
2. Go to your project from command line (Example: 'cd Projects/scrappy-demo') and press enter
3. From project directory type 'node scrappy.js http://somesite.com' in terminal
    (Example: 'node scrappy.js https://www.youmagine.com/designs/lampe')
4. And see result in https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1s0dl-7vjKGrYjwaMBlD88uEJaAeVk0l2ttyszUKjTOU/edit#gid=0


----------------------------------

Simple usage:

If you want to get all images and links you can type:
"node scrapy.js https://www.youmagine.com/designs/" or "node scrapy.js http://www.thingiverse.com/thing"

Or if you want to get images and from specific pages you can type:
"node scrapy.js https://www.youmagine.com/designs/ 1(page from which to start) 10(page on which the complete)" or "node scrapy.js http://www.thingiverse.com/thing 1(page from which to start) 10(page on which the complete)"